title: One man dead in North Austin shooting
content:
Austin Police say two men were fighting on North Lamar Boulevard around 2:30 a.m. on Sunday when one of the men pulled a gun and started shooting.
Austin Travis County EMS says a man in his 30s died at the scene and a woman in her 20s was taken to the hospital with a potentially life-threatening gunshot wound.
EMS took two other woman, in their 20s, to the hospital with non life-threatening gunshot wounds.
APD says one man fled in a vehicle after the shooting.
No arrest has been made at this time.
